Description: Part of a thick-walled cylinder jar of calcite: bears the serekh of Narmer in low relief on the exterior surface. The bottom of the inscription is missing and the stone has been darkened by burning.
Curator's comments: For similar jars see W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' II, pl. II; W. M. F. Petrie, 'Tarkham' II (London, 1914), pl. IV (1982); E.
